OL,7,FZekavica's defence advocate told the
OL,8,Fcourt she offers her "deepest
OL,9,Fapologies" and did not dispute
OL,10,Fcompensation claims.
OL,12,FHe added: "She has lost her home, her
OL,13,Ffamily, her employment, and her
OL,14,Freputation.
OL,16,F"She was homeless, living in a car at
OL,17,Fthe point of her arrest".
OL,19,FIn sentencing, Judge Catherine Fooks
OL,20,Ftold Zekavica her acts were
OL,21,F"detestable and shameful".
